                    "transcript": "[00:00] The recording opens on a wide shot of the courtyard where the ceremony takes place.\n[00:12] A group of elders enters from the east side, carrying the ceremonial loom.\n[00:45] The head weaver welcomes the participants and explains the significance of the pattern being woven this year.\n[02:10] Music begins. Three younger weavers begin passing shuttles in alternating turns.\n[05:30] The ceremony closes with a communal meal served in the same courtyard."
